        "author": {
          "name": "Kit Westneat",
          "email": "kit.westneat@gmail.com",
          "date": "2015-01-05 05:12:47.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-01-16 03:27:05.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6026 tests: modify sanity-sec use right LNET, flush locks",
        "message": "LU-6026 tests: modify sanity-sec use right LNET, flush locks\n\nThere were a couple of spots in sanity-sec that had the @tcp LNET type\nhardcoded in. This caused it to fail on other LNET networks, like\no2ib. This patch uses the $NETTYPES variable to determine the correct\nNID.\n\nThere is also a chance that the client will not flush its locks prior\nto doing the nodemap tests. This patch adds a line to force a flush.\n\nTest-Parameters: alwaysuploadlogs nettypes=o2ib testlist=sanity-sec\nSigned-off-by: Kit Westneat <kit.westneat@gmail.com>\nChange-Id: I68c6400217100939c171ad3707ed834c98a7755a\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/13235\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Jian Yu <jian.yu@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
